OL,3,C'I never thought I'd be scared to be a
OL,4,CJew': ITV News report from Golders
OL,5,CGreen
OL,7,FThe experiences shared with us over
OL,8,Fthe past few weeks paint a picture of
OL,9,Fa community who feel increasingly
OL,10,Funder threat, not only from isolated
OL,11,Fincidents, but from what many view as
OL,12,Fa broader shift in hostility since the
OL,13,FOctober 7 attacks.
OL,15,FFor some, like Baruch and Daniella,
OL,16,Fthe answer is to leave. For others,
OL,17,Fthe hope is simply that Britain can
OL,18,Fonce again become a place where being
OL,19,Fvisibly Jewish no longer feels like an
OL,20,Fact of courage.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G25/33
